  "description": [
    "TOURIST INFLUENCE Boosts Interest In Spanish Food By VIOLET FAULKNER Food Editor of The Star With an increasing number of tourists travel ing to see whether the rain in Spain falls mainly on the plain its not surprising to learn theres a growing interest in Spanish cuisine Contrary to popular opinion Spanish cooking is not hot at all in fact most Spanish dishes are delicately seasoned Betty Wason in her new book The Art of Spanish Cooking published by Dou bleday Co Inc 395 reveals many fascinating se crets pertaining to the food of this southernmost Euro pean country For example meat is often seasoned be fore cooking then allowed to marinate in these seasonings before being cooked she says Olive oil serves as the cata lyst the seasonings are blended with the oil then brushed over the meat Or again as in the recipe be low for larded lamb an olive oilspice mixture is spread over slivers of ham which are Inserted deep in the meat The seasonings then pene trate all through the meat not Just on the surface Since Spain is the worlds chief producer of olive oil its not surprising to find that its used extensively"
  ],
